--- optimizer=ADAM ---   floor: naive (no buffer) = 0.3894
  mechanism      buf=200  buf=500  buf=1000  buf=2000   (forgetting in parens)
  gain-neuron      0.6109     0.7227     0.7229*    0.7256 
                   (0.377)    (0.265)    (0.265)    (0.262)
  gain-synapse     0.7199     0.7108     0.6907*    0.7080 
                   (0.262)    (0.271)    (0.291)    (0.274)

buffer trains ONLY the gate P (main net steps naive, never sees the buffer), so size changes per-task gate calibration, not the backbone: smaller buffer -> fewer distinct past-task exemplars (reservoir evicts the oldest tasks hardest) -> the meta-loss draws k=64 WITH replacement from a narrow pool, so P overfits those exemplars. Oracle + 1-seed caveats carry.
